00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:36.980
6.7 times 10 to the 21.

00:02:36.980 --> 00:02:40.530
So this is the number of Sudoku
grids that there are.

00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:44.650
Now, importantly, what they
were saying is they're not

00:02:44.650 --> 00:02:48.060
saying that every Sudoku grid
can be solved with 17 clues.

00:02:48.060 --> 00:02:51.620
They are saying that there are
no Sudoku grids that can be

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:54.900
